# Workspace Rules LLM Guide

## Purpose

Use this command to validate shared and local rule documents in the current workspace. It checks metadata, section shape, navigation links, reference integrity, and local content-size thresholds.

## When To Run

- After editing local rule documents.
- After syncing or editing shared rule documents.
- After adding or removing rule references.
- Before deciding which local rule documents need optimization.

## How To Read The Result

- A passing result means discovered rule documents satisfy the schema policy.
- Parse errors mean the document could not be inspected safely.
- Reference findings mean linked rule documents or sections do not match what was discovered.
- Structural findings mean the document shape does not match the expected rule contract.
- Local content findings mean a local rule body exceeded `workspace.rules.local.max_content_chars`.

## Examples

- If a navigation reference fails, update the reference to match the discovered rule target.
- If a required section is missing, add the section only when it reflects real guidance.
- If frontmatter is invalid, fix metadata before changing body text.
- If local and shared guidance overlap, keep reusable guidance shared and project-specific guidance local.

## Agent Tips

- Fix parse errors before interpreting other findings.
- Keep rule documents navigable and narrow in purpose.
- Avoid copying shared policy into local rules.
- Rerun after every rule-document edit.
